to reach his psychiatrist.

19:43.080 --> 19:45.450
Oh, well,
where is he?

19:45.510 --> 19:48.350
I'll have to ask him some questions, too.

19:48.420 --> 19:50.950
Dr. Marvin's on vacation
in New Hampshire.

19:51.020 --> 19:53.050
New Hampshire?

19:53.120 --> 19:55.890
I can get him on the phone for you.

19:55.960 --> 19:59.130
Good.
No, don't.

19:59.190 --> 20:00.790
If I really need to,
I can have somebody

20:00.860 --> 20:03.900
from nhpd drop by,
you know.

20:03.970 --> 20:07.740
Uh, but,
what if I wanted to write him a letter?

20:07.800 --> 20:10.370
Would you have a mailing
address of some kind up there?

20:10.440 --> 20:12.710
Oh, sure.

20:12.770 --> 20:16.410
That's, uh,
p.O. Box 14...

20:16.480 --> 20:17.750
Yes?

20:17.810 --> 20:20.980
Lake winnipesaukee.

20:21.050 --> 20:22.380
Which is spelled--

20:22.450 --> 20:24.750
w-I-n-n-I--

20:24.820 --> 20:28.920
[overlapping dialogue]

20:28.990 --> 20:30.790
That's two ns.
- Two es.

20:30.860 --> 20:32.990
E-e, two ns,
two es.

20:33.060 --> 20:35.130
Thank you very much, ladies.

20:35.200 --> 20:39.630
I'm crazy about you,
especially you, Betty.

20:39.700 --> 20:42.370
[Door closes]

20:42.440 --> 20:43.700
[Phone ringing]
- Hmm?

20:43.770 --> 20:46.970
[Mumbles]

20:47.040 --> 20:49.440
[Phone ringing]

20:49.510 --> 20:51.380
Better not be who I think it is.

20:51.450 --> 20:53.010
[Claps]

20:53.080 --> 20:56.580
Hello.

20:56.650 --> 21:00.550
What?

21:00.620 --> 21:02.090
All right.

21:02.160 --> 21:07.730
Thank you for calling, Betty.

21:07.800 --> 21:10.530
It was the service.

21:10.600 --> 21:12.570
That patient,
the one who called before?

21:12.630 --> 21:13.730
Mm-hmm.

21:13.800 --> 21:15.570
He committed suicide.

21:15.640 --> 21:19.470
Oh, Leo,
how horrible.

21:19.540 --> 21:25.080
Oh, well,
let's not let it spoil our vacation.

21:25.150 --> 21:27.950
Baby steps,
get on a bus.

21:28.020 --> 21:30.050
Baby steps,
get on a bus.

21:38.930 --> 21:41.630
[Speaking gibberish]

21:41.700 --> 21:44.730
This is the last bus to
winnipesaukee, Bob.

21:44.800 --> 21:46.830
Yes, I know, wing,
thank you.

21:46.900 --> 21:48.640
Baby steps toward the bus.

21:48.700 --> 21:51.810
Baby steps toward the bus.
Baby steps toward the bus.

21:51.870 --> 21:54.070
Do you think you can do it today, Bob?

21:54.140 --> 21:56.180
We have a baby schedule to keep.

22:05.120 --> 22:08.190
Baby steps get on the bus.

22:08.260 --> 22:12.860
Baby step down the aisle.
Baby step down the aisle.

22:12.930 --> 22:18.070
Baby step...
and sit in the seat.

22:18.130 --> 22:19.970
Hello, I'm Bob.

22:20.040 --> 22:21.540
Would you knock me out, please?

22:21.600 --> 22:22.540
Just hit me in the face.

22:33.310 --> 22:35.480
Do we have enough to feed
the entire film crew, dear?

22:35.550 --> 22:37.990
Honey, we have enough to
feed the entire network.

22:38.050 --> 22:39.650
Oh, great.

22:39.720 --> 22:41.520
Another vacation that's not a vacation.

22:41.590 --> 22:44.390
Why do I have to dress
up for this stupid show?

22:44.460 --> 22:45.860
What do you mean?

22:45.930 --> 22:47.130
You've already tried on
everything you own.

22:47.200 --> 22:48.600
I have not!

22:48.660 --> 22:53.730
All right,
all right, gosh.

22:53.800 --> 22:55.940
It's probably gonna be a
short interview, anyway.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.510
You know, just me and the family,
and my book.

23:05.280 --> 23:07.080
Easy, fella,
we're almost there.

23:09.150 --> 23:12.650
[Vomiting noises]

23:15.790 --> 23:17.490
False alarm.

23:33.910 --> 23:37.850
[Cheering]

23:47.620 --> 23:49.420
Dr. Marvin!

23:49.490 --> 23:52.760
Dr. Leo Marvin!

23:52.830 --> 23:55.760
Dr...Marvin!

23:55.830 --> 23:57.500
Dr. Leo Marvin!

23:57.570 --> 23:58.700
Thank you.

23:58.770 --> 24:00.130
- Good-bye, doctor.
- Thanks again.

24:00.200 --> 24:03.300
Dr...Leo...Marvin!

24:03.370 --> 24:04.810
Honey, is someone calling you?

24:04.870 --> 24:06.510
Dr. Marvin!

24:06.570 --> 24:08.110
Right over there.

24:08.180 --> 24:10.140
Dr. Leo Marvin!

24:10.210 --> 24:11.680
Oh, my God.

24:11.750 --> 24:15.920
Doctor!
Leo!

24:15.980 --> 24:17.020
Leo, do you know that man?

24:17.090 --> 24:18.490
Get in the car.

24:18.550 --> 24:20.620
Come on, hurry, hurry, hurry.

24:20.690 --> 24:22.690
Dr. Marvin!

24:22.760 --> 24:23.620
Oh, ho, ho!

24:23.690 --> 24:25.230
I really appreciate this.

24:25.290 --> 24:28.100
Everyone in the car.
Come on.

24:28.160 --> 24:31.900
Dr. Marvin.
Ha!

24:31.970 --> 24:33.770
Is this a bad time?

24:33.840 --> 24:36.000
[Sighs]

24:36.070 --> 24:37.770
Who's that guy?

24:37.840 --> 24:41.110
Oh, the fam!

24:52.920 --> 24:53.990
Who's that?

24:54.060 --> 24:55.520
I don't know.

24:55.590 --> 24:58.930
What are you doing here?

24:58.990 --> 25:00.760
I thought you were dead.

25:00.830 --> 25:02.600
Oh, no.
They told you.

25:02.660 --> 25:05.330
Well, I fibbed a little bit,
but don't be mad.

25:05.400 --> 25:09.000
Bob, your behavior is
completely inappropriate.

25:09.070 --> 25:10.170
You're angry.

25:10.240 --> 25:11.810
No, no,
I don't get angry.

25:11.870 --> 25:12.870
Well, you're upset.

25:12.940 --> 25:14.340
I don't get upset.

25:14.410 --> 25:15.910
Well, then let's have a little talk.

25:15.980 --> 25:17.410
Bob.

25:17.480 --> 25:19.250
I do not see patients on vacation.

25:19.310 --> 25:20.780
Ever.

25:20.850 --> 25:22.220
How many ways can I make that clear?

25:22.280 --> 25:23.620
Now, what I'd like you to do

25:23.690 --> 25:25.590
is to get on this bus and
go back to New York.

25:25.650 --> 25:27.020
I can't.
I'm totally paralyzed.

25:27.090 --> 25:28.560
I'm all locked up.

25:28.620 --> 25:29.820
You got yourself here.

25:29.890 --> 25:31.330
Barely!

25:31.390 --> 25:33.390
Well, getting back will be therapeutic.

25:33.460 --> 25:34.930
But can't we just have a little talk?

25:35.000 --> 25:36.330
Bob, you are testing my patience.

25:36.400 --> 25:37.870
Come on.
I've come so far.

25:37.930 --> 25:39.000
- Bob!
- I'm baby steppin'.

25:39.070 --> 25:39.970
I'm doing the work.

25:40.040 --> 25:40.970
I'm baby stepping!

25:41.040 --> 25:42.200
I'm not a slacker!

25:42.270 --> 25:43.570
- Listen to me.
- Check it out.

25:43.640 --> 25:45.010
Lookit, I'm in really bad shape.

25:45.070 --> 25:45.870
Come on, please! Please!

25:45.940 --> 25:47.210
Bob, Bob!

25:47.280 --> 25:49.780
Gimme, gimme, gimme!
I need! I need!

25:49.840 --> 25:51.710
Bob, Bob.
Listen, Bob.

25:51.780 --> 25:52.710
Okay, okay!
All right!

25:52.780 --> 25:56.150
All right!
All right!

25:56.220 --> 25:58.050
All right,
it's 2:00.

25:58.120 --> 26:00.220
Go to the bus station,
buy yourself a ticket home,

26:00.290 --> 26:02.260
and then wait for me in that coffee shop.

26:02.320 --> 26:04.090
You'll meet me?

26:04.160 --> 26:08.430
I'll call you...
in two hours.

26:08.500 --> 26:10.230
Oh, my God.
You're the greatest.

26:10.300 --> 26:12.700
No, no.
Just you have to promise me

26:12.770 --> 26:14.230
that you will buy your
ticket and go home.

26:14.300 --> 26:16.340
Absolutely.

26:16.400 --> 26:17.840
I'm gonna do it right now.

26:17.910 --> 26:22.110
All right,
I'll call you at 4:00.

26:22.180 --> 26:24.180
You couldn't possibly make it 3:30,
could you?

26:24.250 --> 26:25.210
Bob!

26:25.280 --> 26:26.980
4:00, 4:00, okay.

26:27.050 --> 26:28.350
Exactly, 4:00.

26:28.420 --> 26:29.880
It's better.

26:29.950 --> 26:32.990
Okay, thank you, Dr. m.

26:33.050 --> 26:36.260
Baby step to 4:00.

26:36.320 --> 26:39.930
Baby step to 4:00.

26:40.000 --> 26:43.160
Baby step to 4:00.

26:43.230 --> 26:47.030
Baby step to 4:00.

26:47.100 --> 26:50.000
Baby step to 4:00.

26:50.070 --> 26:54.270
Baby step to 4:00.

26:54.340 --> 26:56.840
Oh, my gosh!
I need a bowl!

26:56.910 --> 26:58.550
- What?
- A bowl.

26:58.610 --> 27:00.180
He's been locked in
for about eight hours.

27:00.250 --> 27:04.350
He's about to scream.
He's furious.

27:04.420 --> 27:05.920
Sorry, Gil.

27:05.990 --> 27:07.790
A little negligence on my part.

27:07.860 --> 27:08.820
Here you go.
Come on.

27:08.890 --> 27:09.920
Hang tight, fella.

27:09.990 --> 27:12.460
Geronimo!

27:12.530 --> 27:13.890
It was a long ride,
wasn't it?

27:13.960 --> 27:15.160
I know you needed to stretch.

27:15.230 --> 27:17.430
Hey, no, no, no!

27:17.500 --> 27:19.370
I'm expecting a phone call.

27:19.430 --> 27:21.570
Thank you.
Thanks a lot.

27:21.640 --> 27:24.200
Thanks, everybody.
I really appreciate it.

27:24.270 --> 27:28.140
Also, uh,
if I lose consciousness

27:28.210 --> 27:31.750
or black out or something explodes,

27:31.810 --> 27:33.410
would you tell Dr. Marvin when he calls--

27:33.480 --> 27:36.950
- Dr. Leo Marvin?
- Do you know him?

27:37.020 --> 27:40.850
Yeah, he bought our dream house.

27:40.920 --> 27:43.020
Worked a lifetime to save
for a down payment.

27:43.090 --> 27:45.790
And he swooped down
with his bag full of money

27:45.860 --> 27:47.800
and grabbed it out from under us.

27:47.860 --> 27:49.930
Son of a bitch.

27:50.000 --> 27:52.170
She never says that.

27:52.230 --> 27:55.000
Stay as far away from him as possible.

27:55.070 --> 27:56.070
Well, that'll be easy.

27:56.140 --> 27:58.140
He won't see me.

27:58.210 --> 27:59.810
That's why I'm waiting for the phone call.

27:59.870 --> 28:03.180
He won't see you?

28:03.240 --> 28:06.450
Well, we'll show you where he lives.

28:06.510 --> 28:07.950
You will?

28:08.020 --> 28:09.720
The son of a bitch!

28:09.780 --> 28:11.950
She never says that.

28:12.020 --> 28:15.120
Siggy, I have the whole house to fix,
all the art to hang.

28:15.190 --> 28:17.790
I have no idea what I'm
gonna wear on the TV show.

28:17.860 --> 28:20.490
But I have stopped everything in
order to teach you how to dive,

28:20.560 --> 28:22.930
because it is as important
for me to see you dive

28:23.000 --> 28:25.070
<i>as it is for me to appear
on good morning America.</i>

28:25.130 --> 28:26.830
Oh, man,
this is really precious.

28:26.900 --> 28:30.800
Come on,
take off your robe.

28:30.870 --> 28:32.770
Why are you always wearing black?

28:32.840 --> 28:34.580
What is it with you and
this death fixation?

28:34.640 --> 28:38.850
Maybe I'm in mourning
for my lost childhood.

28:38.910 --> 28:41.320
All right, come on.
Come on, turn around.

28:41.380 --> 28:42.550
Toes at the edge.
That's it.

28:42.620 --> 28:43.520
Remember what we learned last year.

28:43.590 --> 28:45.050
Okay, one, two, three, spring.

28:45.120 --> 28:46.390
Now bend at the knees,
bend at the waist,

28:46.450 --> 28:47.720
hands out stiff as a board.

28:47.790 --> 28:51.830
One, two, three, spring.

28:51.890 --> 28:54.900
One, two,

28:54.960 --> 28:58.100
three...

28:58.170 --> 29:00.330
Spring.

29:02.540 --> 29:05.140
Spring... summer, fall.

29:05.210 --> 29:06.840
Time to go, dad.

29:06.910 --> 29:09.510
I don't understand.
Why won't you dive?

29:09.580 --> 29:11.510
With all the horror that's
going on in the world,

29:11.580 --> 29:13.750
what difference does it make?

29:18.120 --> 29:19.250
Hi, Lily.

29:19.320 --> 29:20.920
I'm just calling to remind you

29:20.990 --> 29:23.290
about Leo's surprise party.
Thursday night, 7:00.

29:23.360 --> 29:25.830
Okay?

29:25.890 --> 29:27.530
Well, it'll be after his interview,

29:27.600 --> 29:30.230
so he should be rela--
uh-oh, wait a minute.

29:33.800 --> 29:37.000
Oh, well,
of course I'm thrilled, Lily.

29:37.070 --> 29:39.970
The last person they interviewed
on vacation was Dr. Ruth.

29:40.040 --> 29:41.810
Uh-huh.

29:41.880 --> 29:43.210
Here he comes.

29:43.280 --> 29:44.410
Thursday night, 7:00.
Don't forget.

29:44.480 --> 29:46.450
Okay, bye-bye.

29:53.860 --> 29:55.020
He didn't dive?

29:55.090 --> 29:56.360
No.

29:56.420 --> 29:58.060
Now come on, sweetheart.

29:58.130 --> 29:59.190
He's just a little afraid of it.

29:59.260 --> 30:00.830
Have patience.

30:00.900 --> 30:02.460
It's not like I'm making him jump

30:02.530 --> 30:04.430
out of an airplane or anything.

30:04.500 --> 30:06.770
When I was growing up,
I thought diving was fun.

30:06.840 --> 30:08.670
I thought you were born grown-up, daddy.

30:14.310 --> 30:17.480
Yes, I'd like the number
to the guttmans' coffee--

30:23.790 --> 30:25.790
what are you doing here?
- I'm sorry.

30:25.850 --> 30:27.520
Don't be mad.
The guttmans brought me.

30:27.590 --> 30:29.120
Thank you,
Mr. and Mrs. g.

30:29.190 --> 30:31.260
You're welcome, Bobby.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.290
Hello, Dr. Marvin.

30:33.360 --> 30:35.000
The house looks good.

30:35.060 --> 30:36.960
Burn in hell,
Dr. Marvin!

30:37.030 --> 30:39.200
[Engine turns]

30:42.500 --> 30:44.540
Bob, we agreed that I would call you.

30:44.610 --> 30:47.640
Your coming here is
unbelievably inappropriate.

30:47.710 --> 30:50.480
Dad, can I,
um-- oh, sorry.

30:50.550 --> 30:52.650
Hi, you're Anna,
aren't you?

30:52.710 --> 30:55.280
I saw your picture.
I'm Bob.

30:55.350 --> 30:57.450
Hi, Bob.
Nice to meet you, Bob.

30:57.520 --> 31:00.150
Hi, I'm Bob!

31:00.220 --> 31:01.460
I'm Fay.

31:01.520 --> 31:04.020
Oh, Mrs. m,
you are even prettier

31:04.090 --> 31:05.090
than your picture.

31:05.160 --> 31:06.390
[Chuckles]

31:06.460 --> 31:08.030
And younger.

31:08.100 --> 31:09.630
[Giggles] Thank you.

31:09.700 --> 31:12.700
Fay, Anna,
would you please excuse us?

31:12.770 --> 31:15.400
I think Bob and I have
something to talk about.

31:15.470 --> 31:18.270
Really?
You think so too?

31:18.340 --> 31:20.470
Let's take a walk.

31:20.540 --> 31:22.540
Bob, could I take your fish?

31:22.610 --> 31:24.350
Oh, yes.
Thank you.

31:24.410 --> 31:25.750
He's already eaten.

31:25.810 --> 31:29.320
Don't let him tell you otherwise.

31:29.380 --> 31:31.690
This is a great place.

31:31.750 --> 31:33.450
No wonder the guttmans wanted it.

31:33.520 --> 31:36.320
Whoa!

31:36.390 --> 31:38.230
I'm sorry about barging in here like this.

31:38.290 --> 31:40.660
That's all right.
I understand.

31:40.730 --> 31:42.500
Problems don't go
away just because I do.

31:42.560 --> 31:44.230
[Giggling]

31:44.300 --> 31:46.530
Bob, I'd like you to...

31:46.600 --> 31:49.840
Take a long look around you.

31:49.900 --> 31:52.770
What does everything you
see here have in common?

32:01.220 --> 32:03.350
Vacation, Bob.

32:03.420 --> 32:05.390
Vacation.

32:05.450 --> 32:08.490
Now I can't, Bob,
at this time give you

32:08.560 --> 32:10.220
the kind of therapeutic
attention you need

32:10.290 --> 32:14.090
to solve all your problems
and you know why.

32:14.160 --> 32:15.930
- You're on vacation.
- Exactly.

32:16.000 --> 32:19.500
What I can do is this.

32:19.570 --> 32:21.940
Aww, don't give me pills.

32:22.000 --> 32:23.270
I already have pills.

32:23.340 --> 32:27.640
Uh-uh-uh, this is not pills.

32:27.710 --> 32:30.180
Read it.

32:30.250 --> 32:34.450
It says,
"take a vacation...

32:34.520 --> 32:36.650
From my problems."

32:36.720 --> 32:39.350
I'm giving you permission
to take a vacation, Bob.

32:39.420 --> 32:41.060
Not a vacation from your work

32:41.120 --> 32:42.560
and not a vacation from your daily life,

32:42.620 --> 32:44.490
but a vacation...

32:44.560 --> 32:46.190
From my problems.

32:46.260 --> 32:47.830
Exactly!

32:47.900 --> 32:50.530
Now, I want you to get on that
bus and go back to New York.

32:50.600 --> 32:54.200
But every single time a problem arises,

32:54.270 --> 32:55.700
I want you to take that prescription out

32:55.770 --> 32:57.370
and follow it to the letter.

32:57.440 --> 32:59.270
Doctor's orders.

32:59.340 --> 33:05.280
I'll see you in New York in
my office in one month.

33:05.350 --> 33:08.320
This is incredible.
This is astounding.

33:08.380 --> 33:11.820
For the first time since eselin I feel free.

33:11.890 --> 33:14.220
You've given me a great gift, doctor.

33:14.290 --> 33:17.460
The gift of life.

33:17.530 --> 33:20.330
You're a great man.

33:24.200 --> 33:26.400
I knew coming up here
was the right thing to do.

33:26.470 --> 33:29.400
It feels right because you're here...

33:29.470 --> 33:33.710
And it feels right because you're leaving.

33:33.780 --> 33:36.010
Have a great vacation.

33:36.080 --> 33:39.350
You too, Bob.

33:39.410 --> 33:43.120
A vacation from my problems!

33:43.180 --> 33:47.350
You bet I will!

33:47.420 --> 33:48.790
There you go.

33:48.860 --> 33:52.890
Baby steps.

33:58.430 --> 34:00.170
[Whistling]

34:00.240 --> 34:02.770
[Indistinct chatter]

34:02.840 --> 34:04.370
Is everything all right, honey?

34:04.440 --> 34:05.840
Yes, everything is perfectly fine.

34:05.910 --> 34:07.170
He seemed pleasant enough.

34:07.240 --> 34:10.380
Mm-hmm, when he's controlled.

34:10.449 --> 34:12.650
[Chuckles]

34:12.710 --> 34:15.420
I got so excited I forgot
to bring you with me.

34:15.480 --> 34:17.380
Gil.

34:17.449 --> 34:20.719
Oh, the fish!

34:25.630 --> 34:27.429
Oh, that's a very nice likeness of you.

34:27.500 --> 34:29.600
- Thank you very much.
- Of everyone, actually.

34:29.659 --> 34:32.429
- Bye, Bob.
- Bye-bye, Bob.

34:32.500 --> 34:35.300
Bye-bye.
So long.

34:35.370 --> 34:36.639
You've got to be Sigmund.

34:36.710 --> 34:37.870
Yes, this is Sigmund and this is Bob.

34:37.940 --> 34:39.310
And Bob was just leaving.

34:39.370 --> 34:40.639
Hi.

34:40.710 --> 34:43.580
Oh, this is Gil,
my fish, Sigmund.

34:43.650 --> 34:44.679
Did you get him out of the lake?

34:44.750 --> 34:46.610
No, he's a city fish.

34:46.679 --> 34:48.520
Cool.

34:48.580 --> 34:49.719
But he's loving it up here.

34:49.780 --> 34:51.820
[Chuckles]

34:51.889 --> 34:54.989
Your father is the most
incredible psychiatrist.

34:55.060 --> 34:56.489
I certainly hope you appreciate him.

34:56.560 --> 34:59.660
Have a great vacation, family.

34:59.730 --> 35:02.500
[Quietly] Me too.

35:02.560 --> 35:03.960
Good-bye, Bob.

35:04.030 --> 35:05.300
- Bye, Bob.
- Nice to meet you.

35:05.370 --> 35:06.200
- Good-bye.
- Bye-bye.

35:06.270 --> 35:08.270
Bye.

35:08.340 --> 35:09.470
Well, he's different.

35:09.540 --> 35:10.540
Uh-huh.

35:10.610 --> 35:12.270
Neat fish.

35:12.340 --> 35:14.140
I think I do look younger
than that picture.

35:26.220 --> 35:28.990
Or...

35:37.970 --> 35:39.600
[Grunts]

35:39.670 --> 35:43.770
[Humming]

35:43.840 --> 35:44.910
[Chuckles]

35:44.970 --> 35:47.410
This?

35:47.480 --> 35:48.880
I told you I like the rifle.

35:48.940 --> 35:50.880
I think it's a symbol of virility.

35:50.950 --> 35:52.510
Now can I eat breakfast?

35:52.580 --> 35:54.280
I'm supposed to go sailing
on George stark's boat.

35:54.350 --> 35:56.850
Wait, wait, wait.

35:56.920 --> 35:58.690
Fay, I need your opinion.

35:58.750 --> 36:01.090
Rifle or bust?

36:01.160 --> 36:03.590
I think both look so wonderful, sweetie.

36:03.660 --> 36:07.060
Oh, Fay.

36:07.130 --> 36:09.530
You know I can't live
with that kind of answer.

36:09.600 --> 36:11.570
I need-- I need feedback.

36:11.630 --> 36:15.600
[Bell ringing]

36:21.280 --> 36:23.740
Good morning,
Dr. Marvin.

36:23.810 --> 36:25.880
No, these aren't for you.

36:25.950 --> 36:28.620
They're for Fay...
for yesterday

36:28.680 --> 36:30.220
for your hospitality to Gil and me.

36:30.290 --> 36:32.220
I didn't say thank you.

36:32.290 --> 36:33.650
I thought about what you said.

36:33.720 --> 36:37.460
Take a vacation from
my problems and I did.

36:37.530 --> 36:39.930
- But you're back.
- No, I'm not.

36:40.000 --> 36:42.600
- You're not?
- No, I'm not.

36:42.660 --> 36:45.030
I'm on vacation.

36:45.100 --> 36:48.200
This isn't an appointment.
I'm dropping by.

36:48.270 --> 36:50.300
This is my first time over the lake.

36:50.370 --> 36:53.940
This is my first time anywhere.

36:54.010 --> 36:55.840
I'm a little anxious 'cause
I haven't figured out

36:55.910 --> 36:58.110
how to get food yet,
but I'm staying at the guttmans'.

36:58.180 --> 36:59.780
When I told them what you said,
they insisted.

36:59.850 --> 37:01.320
No, no, no, no, no!

37:01.380 --> 37:03.680
So, I know we can't work,

37:03.750 --> 37:05.520
but let's get the friendship thing going.

37:05.590 --> 37:07.320
See you later.

37:07.390 --> 37:09.420
Sure seems like he's staying,
doesn't it?

37:09.490 --> 37:13.490
Hey, paper boy,
this was on your porch.

37:13.560 --> 37:16.430
Thank you.

37:25.110 --> 37:27.540
Family conference!
Family conference!

37:27.610 --> 37:29.310
All right.

37:29.380 --> 37:31.110
Now, I don't want any of you

37:31.180 --> 37:32.950
letting Bob into this house.

37:33.010 --> 37:35.080
- Why?
- Why?

37:35.150 --> 37:37.650
Sweetheart, aren't you
overreacting just a little bit?

37:37.720 --> 37:39.320
Good, I'm glad we're all in agreement.

37:39.390 --> 37:42.360
Family conference is over.

37:42.420 --> 37:45.930
[Chuckling]

37:45.990 --> 37:48.930
Vacation from my problems.

37:49.000 --> 37:50.860
There's nobody here.

37:50.930 --> 37:52.800
There's nothing to fear.

37:52.870 --> 37:54.740
There's nobody here.

37:54.800 --> 37:56.770
I'm completely alone.

37:56.840 --> 38:01.740
I'm all by myself.

38:01.810 --> 38:03.440
There's nobody here!

38:03.510 --> 38:07.080
Oh!

38:07.150 --> 38:11.220
There's nobody here!

38:22.830 --> 38:24.700
- Hi, Bob.
- Hi.

38:24.770 --> 38:27.430
- Where ya going?
- Just going to town.

38:27.500 --> 38:28.900
Buy some kleenex.

38:28.970 --> 38:30.700
Well, you want a ride?

38:30.770 --> 38:33.640
I'd love one.

38:37.610 --> 38:40.080
Do a lot of people use this car?

38:40.150 --> 38:42.580
Just us.

38:55.760 --> 38:58.630
So what's it like being the
daughter of a brilliant analyst

38:58.700 --> 38:59.900
who's sleeping in the next bedroom

38:59.970 --> 39:01.000
at night when you need him?

39:01.070 --> 39:05.170
Is it great?

39:05.240 --> 39:09.080
No, it's not great.

39:09.140 --> 39:11.780
I have problems the
same as anyone else.

39:11.850 --> 39:13.610
The same as you.

39:13.680 --> 39:15.650
You're afraid your bladder will explode?

39:15.720 --> 39:16.980
What other ones are the same?

39:17.050 --> 39:18.990
Like what?
Like what?

39:19.050 --> 39:21.220
Well, like analyzing everything tdeath

39:21.290 --> 39:23.490
to see if what I'm feeling is normal.

39:23.560 --> 39:25.860
Yes, I have that.

39:25.930 --> 39:28.900
Do you freeze up and turn
into wood when you're around

39:28.960 --> 39:30.630
a good-looking guy and
you don't even know

39:30.700 --> 39:32.170
if he likes you or not?

39:32.230 --> 39:33.900
Well, not a guy, but, yes,
I freeze--

39:33.970 --> 39:35.400
you know what I do?

39:35.470 --> 39:37.670
I treat people as if they were telephones.

39:37.740 --> 39:39.840
If I meet somebody who I don't
think likes me, I say to myself,

39:39.910 --> 39:43.210
"Bob, this one is just
temporarily out of order.

39:43.280 --> 39:44.140
"You know,
don't break the connection.

39:44.210 --> 39:46.880
Just hang up and try again."

39:46.950 --> 39:49.680
- And does it work?
- It seems to be.

39:49.750 --> 39:54.320
I'm on vacation at lake winnipesaukee,
aren't I?

39:54.390 --> 39:56.590
Do you want to come sailing with me

39:56.660 --> 39:57.760
on my friend George's boat?

39:57.830 --> 39:59.930
No, no.

40:00.000 --> 40:02.260
That's okay.
You don't have to.

40:02.330 --> 40:04.870
No, I'd love to.
[Chuckles]

40:04.930 --> 40:06.170
It sounds great.

40:06.230 --> 40:08.540
I've never been on a boat

40:08.600 --> 40:10.940
and I don't think I could handle it.

40:11.010 --> 40:13.870
It just makes my lips
numb to think about it.

40:13.940 --> 40:15.610
But if your friend is a good sailor

40:15.680 --> 40:18.850
and the craft is seaworthy, yes,
I will go sailing.

40:18.910 --> 40:20.680
Yeah, let's go sailing.

40:20.750 --> 40:23.820
I have no other plans.

40:23.890 --> 40:26.250
I'm sailing!

40:26.320 --> 40:29.790
I'm sailing!

40:29.860 --> 40:33.830
I'm sailing!

40:33.900 --> 40:37.230
I'm sailing!

40:37.300 --> 40:39.270
I'm sailing!
I'm sailing!

40:39.330 --> 40:44.670
I'm sailing!

40:44.740 --> 40:47.010
This is child abuse.

40:47.080 --> 40:49.910
If you drop me,
I'll prosecute.

40:49.980 --> 40:52.150
I'm not gonna let go
until you're ready, okay?

40:52.210 --> 40:53.880
Trust me.

40:53.950 --> 40:57.990
Put your hands out like I showed you.

40:58.050 --> 40:59.220
I'm not ready.

40:59.290 --> 41:00.790
You hear me?
I'm not ready.

41:00.860 --> 41:02.690
Don't drop me.
I'm not ready.

41:02.760 --> 41:05.660
Dr. Marvin,
I'm sailing!

41:05.730 --> 41:07.800
Whoa!

41:07.860 --> 41:10.000
- How about that, doc?
- Oh, Siggy.

41:10.070 --> 41:11.870
Oh, oh!

41:11.930 --> 41:14.970
Murderer!

41:15.040 --> 41:17.000
Hitler!

41:17.070 --> 41:19.310
Hi, dad!

41:19.370 --> 41:22.410
I sail!

41:31.290 --> 41:33.220
Anna!

41:33.290 --> 41:34.720
Anna, come here, please.

41:34.790 --> 41:36.520
Dad?

41:36.590 --> 41:38.260
Anna, I'd like to speak to you, please.

41:38.330 --> 41:39.960
Dr. Marvin, Dr. Marvin,
guess what.

41:40.030 --> 41:41.400
Ahoy!

41:41.460 --> 41:44.300
I sail.
I'm a sailor. I sail.

41:44.370 --> 41:45.930
I'd like to talk to my daughter alone.

41:46.000 --> 41:47.230
But isn't this a breakthrough?

41:47.300 --> 41:49.340
I mean,
that I'm a sailor.

41:49.400 --> 41:51.910
I sail.

41:51.970 --> 41:53.170
I sail now.

41:53.240 --> 41:55.110
Keep sailing, Bob.

41:55.180 --> 41:56.680
Out on a boat on the lake

41:56.750 --> 41:58.450
way far away from the dock

41:58.510 --> 42:01.220
into the wind with the
sky and everything.

42:01.280 --> 42:02.980
Ahoy!

42:03.050 --> 42:05.790
I thought I told you to
stay away from Bob Wiley.

42:05.850 --> 42:07.960
Daddy, I was with my friends.

42:08.020 --> 42:09.890
Where are we going?
- Home.

42:09.960 --> 42:11.790
- Well, what about the car?
- Leave it.

42:11.860 --> 42:13.060
It's been a long time since

42:13.130 --> 42:15.760
I've had a talk with my daughter.

42:15.830 --> 42:17.800
Oh, daddy,
not here.

42:17.870 --> 42:22.040
Anna, Anna, Anna, Anna.

42:22.100 --> 42:23.770
[Sighs]

42:23.840 --> 42:26.340
Anna, I know you won't
listen to your father,

42:26.410 --> 42:28.280
but you always listen to me.

42:28.340 --> 42:30.240
So I'm asking you not to see Bob Wiley.

42:30.310 --> 42:31.710
Daddy, I am just--

42:31.780 --> 42:32.810
I can't hear you.

42:32.880 --> 42:33.810
Where are you, Anna?

42:33.880 --> 42:37.480
Ooh!

42:37.550 --> 42:40.090
I am just having fun with my friends.

42:40.160 --> 42:42.860
- And Bob Wiley.
- Yes, and Bob Wiley.

42:42.920 --> 42:44.530
Bob Wiley is your father's patient.

42:44.590 --> 42:46.760
Bob Wiley is a very sensitive person.

42:46.830 --> 42:48.160
Your father's sensitive.

42:48.230 --> 42:49.500
Bob listens to people.

42:49.560 --> 42:51.170
Your father listens to people!

42:51.230 --> 42:53.270
Except when he's up here
in lake winnipesaukee.

42:53.340 --> 42:54.940
[Sighs]

42:55.000 --> 42:57.270
He is fun!

42:57.340 --> 42:58.970
Ugh!

42:59.040 --> 43:02.340
Your father's...
kind of fun.

43:05.150 --> 43:08.680
I'm Fay Marvin,
Dr. Marvin's wife...

43:08.750 --> 43:11.820
And I'm very happy to
be on your program.

43:11.890 --> 43:14.760
And these are our children,
Anna and Siggy.

43:32.340 --> 43:34.740
- I'm a failure.
- What?

43:34.810 --> 43:36.280
I'm going on national television tomorrow

43:36.340 --> 43:38.380
as an expert in human behavior

43:38.450 --> 43:39.980
and in the space of the last hour,

43:40.050 --> 43:45.120
both of my children have
told me that they hate me.

43:45.190 --> 43:47.760
Come on,
you know they don't mean it.

43:47.820 --> 43:52.490
Anna accused me of being insensitive.

43:52.560 --> 43:56.460
No.
No.

43:56.530 --> 43:58.900
What she actually said was

43:58.970 --> 44:01.840
I was insensitive and I didn't listen

44:01.900 --> 44:05.070
and I wasn't any fun

44:05.140 --> 44:07.910
and that Bob Wiley was.

44:07.980 --> 44:11.180
♪ give me some time ♪

44:11.250 --> 44:14.580
♪ to blow the man down ♪

44:24.390 --> 44:27.430
notice anything different about me?

44:27.500 --> 44:30.100
- No.
- Do you sail?

44:30.170 --> 44:31.470
No.

44:31.530 --> 44:32.800
Well, I just picked it up.

44:32.870 --> 44:34.170
[Chuckles]

44:34.240 --> 44:36.800
Wonder what I'm going to pick up next.

44:36.870 --> 44:40.270
- Try diving.
- All right, diving.

44:40.340 --> 44:43.010
I know a great teacher.

44:43.080 --> 44:45.110
[Sighs] I mean,
my dad,

44:45.180 --> 44:48.450
he just dropped me in the
water without warning me first.

44:48.520 --> 44:50.650
I mean,
I nearly drowned.

44:50.720 --> 44:53.050
My whole life flashed before my eyes.

44:53.120 --> 44:54.490
Well, you're lucky you're only 12.

44:54.560 --> 44:56.590
It was still grim.

44:56.660 --> 44:58.360
What is it with him and diving?

44:58.430 --> 45:00.330
What's the big deal?

45:00.400 --> 45:03.200
Well, he,
he prob--whoa.

45:06.470 --> 45:08.070
He probably just wants you to beat it.

45:08.140 --> 45:09.570
That's all.

45:09.640 --> 45:11.070
You know,
he probably just wants you to dive

45:11.140 --> 45:13.370
because you're afraid of diving.

45:13.440 --> 45:18.650
Did I tell you I sailed on my first try?

45:18.710 --> 45:19.880
I just let the boat do the work.

45:19.950 --> 45:23.180
That was my secret.

45:23.250 --> 45:25.890
But with diving,
what is the, uh--

45:25.950 --> 45:27.650
what's the thing?
What's the trick?

45:27.720 --> 45:30.560
I don't know.
It's supposed to be easy.

45:30.630 --> 45:36.130
Well, can you give me a handle on it?

45:36.200 --> 45:38.270
Thanks.

45:38.330 --> 45:41.000
Careful.
Oh, careful!

45:41.070 --> 45:42.200
Let's go to the edge.

45:42.270 --> 45:44.640
- Careful.
- Go to the edge.

45:44.710 --> 45:47.410
Come on, toes up,
toes up, to the edge.

45:47.480 --> 45:48.180
Don't worry.
Come on.

45:48.240 --> 45:49.680
Right here.

45:49.740 --> 45:50.940
Let's call this the edge right here.

45:51.010 --> 45:53.480
Okay, then step up to the edge.

45:53.550 --> 45:55.120
Well, then walk up to our edge.

45:55.180 --> 45:58.220
Okay, got you.

45:58.290 --> 46:00.420
Now bend your knees.
Bend your knees.

46:00.490 --> 46:03.490
Very good.

46:03.560 --> 46:06.630
Bend your knees and be stiff as a board.

46:06.700 --> 46:08.600
I am stiff as a board.

46:08.660 --> 46:10.530
Now, lean forward.
Lean.

46:10.600 --> 46:12.300
All right, just a second.
Don't rush it.

46:12.370 --> 46:13.370
Just a second.

46:13.440 --> 46:16.500
This is my first dive.

46:16.570 --> 46:18.770
Okay, lean.
Lean.

46:18.840 --> 46:21.210
Wait, I can't see what you're doing.

46:21.280 --> 46:25.210
Why don't you get in front?

46:25.280 --> 46:26.950
All right, careful.
Hold it, hold it, hold it.

46:27.020 --> 46:28.280
Wait, wait.
- Okay, come on, come on.

46:28.350 --> 46:30.150
Now hold my shirt.

46:30.220 --> 46:31.620
I'll show you what we're supposed to do.

46:31.690 --> 46:33.250
I got it.

46:33.320 --> 46:34.790
- Okay.
- All right.

46:34.860 --> 46:37.190
- And bend my knees.
- Bend your knees.

46:37.260 --> 46:38.590
Lean forward.
Arms out.

46:38.660 --> 46:41.130
Arms out straight.
Stiff as a board.

46:41.200 --> 46:43.430
Honey, come here.
Look.

46:43.500 --> 46:45.370
Bend over.

46:45.430 --> 46:47.000
- Come here.
- All right, I got ya.

46:47.070 --> 46:48.740
I got ya.

46:53.040 --> 46:54.380
I don't want to have to see this.

46:54.440 --> 46:56.340
No, please.
- One.

46:56.410 --> 46:57.610
- No.
- Two.

46:57.680 --> 46:59.210
Don't do it, please!

46:59.280 --> 47:02.180
Three.

47:06.520 --> 47:08.420
- Yes.
- Yeah!

47:08.490 --> 47:10.390
Yeah.

47:10.460 --> 47:13.260
- Bravo, Siggy!
- Good boy!

47:13.330 --> 47:15.330
Very nice, Bob!
Thank you!

47:15.400 --> 47:16.600
Thank you!

47:16.670 --> 47:18.500
I'll take it from here.

47:18.570 --> 47:20.500
You dove.
That's wonderful.

47:20.570 --> 47:22.470
Did you see me dive, dad?

47:22.540 --> 47:24.070
Did you see me dive?
I dove!

47:24.140 --> 47:25.340
Thank you.
Excellent.

47:25.410 --> 47:26.370
Watch this!
I can do it again.

47:26.440 --> 47:27.640
I'll take it from here.

47:27.710 --> 47:28.940
Did you see, dad?

47:29.010 --> 47:30.110
Here, I'm gonna do it again.

47:30.180 --> 47:31.210
Thank you very much.

47:31.280 --> 47:32.150
That was very nice.

47:32.210 --> 47:33.480
Ow!

47:33.550 --> 47:35.320
[Overlapping chatter]

47:35.380 --> 47:37.350
- Bob!
- Bob!

47:37.420 --> 47:38.590
Kick your feet, Bob!

47:38.650 --> 47:41.420
- Ooh!
- Keep breathing.

47:41.490 --> 47:44.290
- Keep breathing.
- Bob, catch!

47:44.360 --> 47:45.860
What are you staring at?

47:45.930 --> 47:49.630
I had every right to buy this house!

47:49.700 --> 47:52.170
Come on,
kick harder.

47:52.230 --> 47:55.570
Oh!

47:55.640 --> 47:57.070
Am I gonna die?

47:57.140 --> 48:00.110
[Overlapping chatter]

48:00.180 --> 48:01.440
- Bob?
- Help.

48:01.510 --> 48:05.610
He's over here.

48:05.680 --> 48:07.180
- Bob!
- Am I gonna die?

48:07.250 --> 48:10.380
No!

48:10.450 --> 48:12.420
[Raspberries]

48:16.090 --> 48:18.160
Fay.

48:23.370 --> 48:25.400
Look, everybody,
I'm not wrong often,

48:25.470 --> 48:27.100
but when I am I admit it.

48:27.170 --> 48:29.170
I mean it.

48:29.240 --> 48:31.370
I would like you all to accept my apology.

48:31.440 --> 48:32.710
Well, what about Bob?

48:32.770 --> 48:34.040
What about Bob?

48:34.110 --> 48:35.540
Yeah, dad.

48:35.610 --> 48:37.380
Don't you think you
should apologize to Bob?

48:37.450 --> 48:39.710
I will not apologize to Bob.

48:39.780 --> 48:42.320
Why not?

48:42.380 --> 48:45.850
All right,
I'll apologize to Bob.

48:53.800 --> 48:55.930
And now I'd like him to go.

48:56.000 --> 48:59.570
Leo, why are you so
hostile to the poor man?

48:59.630 --> 49:02.070
Because he's a patient.

49:02.140 --> 49:03.740
Fay, don't you get it?

49:03.810 --> 49:05.170
He's a patient.

49:05.240 --> 49:07.340
A patient.
A patient.

49:07.410 --> 49:09.510
Mom, can we have Bob over for dinner?

49:09.580 --> 49:11.910
- Dinner?
- Yeah!

49:11.980 --> 49:13.580
I don't want Bob for dinner, Fay.

49:13.650 --> 49:15.280
Leo, it's for the kids.

49:15.350 --> 49:17.350
I don't want Bob for dinner.

49:17.420 --> 49:21.820
Fay, I want to think about
my interview tomorrow.

49:21.890 --> 49:25.890
I'm sorry, Leo.
Right is right.

